# Church Directory Project Overview & Development Log

## 1. Project Purpose

The goal of this project is to create a **modern, mobile-friendly church member directory** that is easy for church members to browse and easy for church administrators to maintain.

The system is designed with three main priorities:

1. **Simple for members to use**
2. **Simple for church staff to maintain**
3. **Secure access to member information**

The directory will ultimately run as a **web application hosted on GitHub Pages**, with **Firebase handling authentication and data access**, while **Airtable serves as the administrative database interface** for church staff.

This architecture allows the church to manage the directory **without needing technical knowledge**.

---

# 2. System Architecture

The project is composed of four major components.

## Airtable (Administrative Database)

Airtable will act as the **data management system for church administrators**.

Church staff will be able to:

* Add members
* Update member contact information
* Upload photos
* Manage households
* Track ministries
* Update birthdays and anniversaries

Airtable is used because it provides:

* Spreadsheet-style editing
* Simple media uploads
* Easy filtering and searching
* Low technical barrier for staff

However, the public website will **not connect directly to Airtable** for security reasons.

---

## Firebase (Backend Layer)

Firebase will act as the **secure backend layer** between Airtable and the directory website.

Firebase responsibilities will include:

* Authentication (member login)
* Secure API endpoints
* Data syncing from Airtable
* Hosting optional future features
* Preventing unauthorized access

Firebase ensures:

* Only approved users can access the directory
* Member data is not exposed publicly
* Access can be revoked if needed

---

## GitHub Pages (Hosting)

The directory web app will be hosted using **GitHub Pages**.

Advantages:

* Free hosting
* Extremely reliable
* Version control
* Easy updates through Git

The directory itself is a **static web application** consisting of:

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript

Because the site is static, it loads very quickly and is easy to maintain.

---

## The Directory Web App

The directory interface provides members with a clean, modern way to view church members.

Features include:

* Photo-based member cards
* Member profile pages
* Household grouping
* Search functionality
* Mobile-friendly design
* Tap-to-call phone numbers
* Tap-to-email addresses
* Tap-to-open maps for addresses

The directory is designed to behave more like a **mobile app experience** than a traditional website.

